  <main id="main-doc">
    <section class="main-section" id="Introduction">
      <header>Introduction</header>
      <p>The peanut butter and jelly sandwich is a basic meal that many people enjoy. </p>
      <p>It is important to follow each step carefully.</p>
      <code>A peanut butter and jelly sandwich includes bread, peanut butter, and jelly.</code>
      <ul>
        <li>Simple process</li>
        <li>Common ingredients</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="main-section" id="Ingredients">
      <header>Ingredients</header>
      <p>You only need three ingredients to make this sandwich.</p>
      <p>Fresh ingredients will taste better.</p>
      <code>Ingredients: peanut butter, jelly, bread.</code>
      <ul>
        <li>Peanut butter</li>
        <li>Jlly</li>
        <li>Bread</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="main-section" id="Tools">
      <header>Tools</header>
      <p>You only need a few tools to make this sandwich. The process is simple and does not require any sharp items. Clean tools prevent contamination.</p>
      <p>Use a butter knife to spread each ingredient smoothly without damaging the bread.</p>
      <code>A butter knife works well for spreading both ingredients.</code>
    </section>

    <section class="main-section" id="Steps">
      <header>Steps</header>
      <p>The process involves preparing the slices of bread and applying each spread. Follow the steps in order to avoid mess and waste. Do not use too much of either spread.</p>
      <p>Spreading evenly makes the sandwich easier to eat.</p>
      <code>
        Step 1: Spread peanut butter on one slice.<br>
        Step 2: Spread jelly on the other slice.<br>
        Step 3: Press the slices together.
      </code>
      <ul>
        <li>Place both slices of bread on a surface</li>
        <li>Spread peanut butter on one slice</li>
        <li>Spread jelly on the second slice</li>
        <li>Press the slices together carefully</li>
        <li>Cut in half if desired</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="main-section" id="Extras">
      <header>Extras</header>
      <p>This section includes extra information that can improve your experience.</p>
      <p>Small additions can make the sandwich better without changing the main steps.</p>
      <code>Optional: Use different breads or add a banana for more flavor.</code>
      <ul>
        <li>Use whole wheat bread for more fiber</li>
        <li>Try crunchy or creamy peanut butter</li>
        <li>Add sliced bananas</li>
        <li>Press the sandwich firmly for clean cuts</li>
        <li>Pack into a lunchbox if your taking it to school.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
